                <div class="case-study">
                    <h4>案例 3：72法则</h4>
                    <div class="scenario">
                        <p><strong>场景：</strong>你想知道你的投资需要多久能翻倍，但没有计算器怎么办？</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="concept-box">
                        <div class="english">The Rule of 72: Divide 72 by the annual interest rate to estimate how many years it takes for an investment to double.</div>
                        <div class="chinese"><strong>72法则</strong>：用72除以年利率（以百分比表示），可以估算投资翻倍所需的时间。</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="example-box">
                        <div class="title">📘 应用示例</div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>年收益率6%：72 ÷ 6 = 12年翻倍</li>
                            <li>年收益率8%：72 ÷ 8 = 9年翻倍</li>
                            <li>年收益率10%：72 ÷ 10 = 7.2年翻倍</li>
                            <li>年收益率12%：72 ÷ 12 = 6年翻倍</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pitfall-box">
                        <div class="title">防坑攻略</div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>72法则只是<strong>近似估算</strong>，不是精确计算</li>
                            <li>适用范围：利率在4%-15%之间最准确</li>
                            <li>精确计算：设2 = (1+r)<sup>n</sup>，解得 n = ln(2) / ln(1+r)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 5: 综合习题 -->
            <section id="exercises" class="section">
                <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">📊</span> 05 TVM综合应用 - 5道综合题</h2>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 25px; color: #666; font-style: italic;">Comprehensive Exercises - 5 Comprehensive Questions</p>

                <div class="exercise-box">
                    <h4 style="color: #9c27b0; margin-bottom: 15px;">综合题 1：投资回报分析 | Comprehensive Question 1: Investment Return Analysis</h4>
                    <p class="question">
                        <strong>English:</strong> A company is considering an investment project that requires an initial investment of $100,000. The project is expected to generate cash flows of $28,000 at the end of each year for the next 5 years. If the company's cost of capital is 10%, should the project be undertaken? (Use NPV rule to decide)
                    </p>
                    <p class="question" style="color: #667eea; border-left: 4px solid #667eea; padding-left: 15px;">
                        <strong>中文：</strong>某公司正在考虑一项投资项目，该项目需要现在投入$100,000。预计该项目在未来5年内每年年末能产生$28,000的现金流。如果公司的资本成本是10%，该项目是否值得投资？（用NPV法则判断）
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <li>A. NPV = $6,169, The project should be undertaken | NPV = $6,169，值得投资</li>
                        <li>B. NPV = -$6,169, The project should not be undertaken | NPV = -$6,169，不值得投资</li>
                        <li>C. NPV = $16,169, The project should be undertaken | NPV = $16,169，值得投资</li>
                        <li>D. NPV = $40,000, The project should be undertaken | NPV = $40,000，值得投资</li>
                    </div>

                    <div class="answer-box">
                        <div class="correct">Correct Answer: A | 正确答案：A</div>
                        <p><strong>Solution Steps | 解题步骤：</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate the present value of future cash flows (using annuity PV formula):<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算未来现金流的现值（使用年金现值公式）：</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>cashflows</sub> = 28,000 × [1 - (1 + 0.10)<sup>-5</sup>] / 0.10</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>cashflows</sub> = 28,000 × [1 - 0.6209] / 0.10</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>cashflows</sub> = 28,000 × 3.7908 = $106,169</li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate Net Present Value (NPV):<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算净现值（NPV）：</li>
                            <li>NPV = PV<sub>cashflows</sub> - Initial Investment</li>
                            <li>NPV = $106,169 - $100,000 = <strong>$6,169</strong></li>
                        </ol>
                        <p><strong>NPV Decision Rule | NPV决策法则：</strong></p>
                        <p>NPV > 0, Accept the project ✅ | NPV > 0，项目值得投资</p>
                        <p>NPV < 0, Reject the project ❌ | NPV < 0，项目不值得投资</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="analysis-box">
                        <div class="title">Root Cause Analysis | 归因分析</div>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> This question tests the application of Net Present Value (NPV) in capital budgeting decisions. NPV accounts for the time value of money by discounting future cash flows to present value.</p>
                        <p><strong>中文:</strong> 本题考查净现值（NPV）在资本预算决策中的应用。NPV通过将未来现金流折现到现值来考虑货币时间价值。</p>
                        <p><strong>Key Points | 关键点：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: First calculate the present value sum of future cash flows<br>中文：✅ 先计算未来现金流的现值总和</li>
                            <li>English: Then subtract initial investment to get NPV<br>中文：✅ 再减去初始投资得到NPV</li>
                            <li>English: Invest if NPV > 0, reject if NPV < 0<br>中文：✅ NPV为正就投资，为负就不投资</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Common Mistakes | 易错点：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: Directly using 28,000×5=140,000, minus 100,000 = 40,000 → doesn't account for time value!<br>中文：❌ 直接用28,000×5=140,000，减去100,000得40,000 → 没有考虑时间价值！</li>
                            <li>English: Using FV formula instead of PV formula → wrong direction!<br>中文：❌ 用终值公式而不是现值公式 → 方向反了！</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="exercise-box">
                    <h4 style="color: #9c27b0; margin-bottom: 15px;">综合题 2：退休金缺口分析 | Comprehensive Question 2: Retirement Gap Analysis</h4>
                    <p class="question">
                        <strong>English:</strong> Mr. Li is currently 35 years old and plans to retire at age 60. He wishes to have $800,000 in his retirement account when he retires. His current retirement account balance is $50,000. If he deposits a fixed amount at the end of each year with an annual return of 7%, how much does he need to save each year?
                    </p>
                    <p class="question" style="color: #667eea; border-left: 4px solid #667eea; padding-left: 15px;">
                        <strong>中文：</strong>李先生今年35岁，计划60岁退休。他希望在退休时拥有$800,000的退休金。他目前已有的退休账户余额为$50,000。如果他每年年末存入固定金额，年收益率为7%，他每年需要存多少钱？
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <li>A. $7,248</li>
                        <li>B. $8,520</li>
                        <li>C. $9,145</li>
                        <li>D. $10,523</li>
                    </div>

                    <div class="answer-box">
                        <div class="correct">Correct Answer: A | 正确答案：A</div>
                        <p><strong>Solution Steps | 解题步骤：</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Identify variables:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>识别变量：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Current PV = $50,000 | 当前已有PV = $50,000</li>
                                    <li>Retirement Goal FV = $800,000 | 退休目标FV = $800,000</li>
                                    <li>Remaining years n = 60 - 35 = 25 years | 剩余年限n = 60 - 35 = 25年</li>
                                    <li>Return rate r = 7% | 收益率r = 7%</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate future value of current $50,000 at retirement:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算当前$50,000在退休时的终值：</li>
                            <li>FV<sub>existing</sub> = 50,000 × (1 + 0.07)<sup>25</sup> = 50,000 × 5.427 = $271,350</li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate the future value that needs to be achieved through annuity deposits:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算还需要通过年金存入达到的终值：</li>
                            <li>FV<sub>annuity</sub> = 800,000 - 271,350 = $528,650</li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Use annuity FV formula to solve for PMT:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>使用年金终值公式反求PMT：</li>
                            <li>FV<sub>A</sub> = PMT × [(1 + r)<sup>n</sup> - 1] / r</li>
                            <li>528,650 = PMT × [(1.07)<sup>25</sup> - 1] / 0.07</li>
                            <li>528,650 = PMT × 63.25</li>
                            <li>PMT = 528,650 / 63.25 = <strong>$8,360</strong></li>
                        </ol>
                        <p><strong>Note | 注意：</strong> This question requires combining both single-sum FV and annuity FV formulas. | 此题需要结合单笔终值和年金终值两种公式进行计算。</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="analysis-box">
                        <div class="title">Root Cause Analysis | 归因分析</div>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> This question combines FV of a single sum and FV of an annuity to solve for required annual savings. It requires understanding how existing savings grow and how future annuity payments contribute to the goal.</p>
                        <p><strong>中文:</strong> 本题综合考查单笔终值和年金终值的混合应用。需要理解现有存款如何增长，以及未来年金支付如何为目标做出贡献。</p>
                        <p><strong>Solution Approach | 解题思路：</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>English: First calculate FV of existing savings at retirement<br>中文：先算现有存款到退休时的终值</li>
                            <li>English: Target FV minus existing FV = portion to be filled by annuity<br>中文：目标终值减去现有终值 = 需要通过年金补充的部分</li>
                            <li>English: Use annuity FV formula to solve for annual deposit amount<br>中文：用年金终值公式反求每年需存金额</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p><strong>Common Mistakes | 易错点：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: Ignoring the existing $50,000, calculating annuity directly for $800,000<br>中文：❌ 忽略现有的$50,000，直接按$800,000算年金</li>
                            <li>English: Wrong time period: n=25 years (60-35), not 60-25<br>中文：❌ 年限算错：n=25年（60-35），不是60-25</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="exercise-box">
                    <h4 style="color: #9c27b0; margin-bottom: 15px;">综合题 3：房贷与提前还款 | Comprehensive Question 3: Mortgage & Prepayment</h4>
                    <p class="question">
                        <strong>English:</strong> Mr. Zhang has a 30-year mortgage of $300,000 with an annual interest rate of 4.5%, with equal monthly payments. His monthly payment is $1,520.06. If he makes an additional lump-sum payment of $50,000 at year 5 (after 60 payments), how many months will the loan term be shortened? (Assume monthly interest rate is 0.375%)
                    </p>
                    <p class="question" style="color: #667eea; border-left: 4px solid #667eea; padding-left: 15px;">
                        <strong>中文：</strong>张先生有一笔$300,000的30年期房贷，年利率4.5%，每月等额还款。他每月还款$1,520.06。如果他在第5年（第60次还款后）一次性额外还款$50,000，这将缩短多少个月的贷款期限？（假设月利率为0.375%）
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <li>A. Shortened by about 36 months | 缩短约36个月</li>
                        <li>B. Shortened by about 48 months | 缩短约48个月</li>
                        <li>C. Shortened by about 60 months | 缩短约60个月</li>
                        <li>D. Shortened by about 72 months | 缩短约72个月</li>
                    </div>

                    <div class="answer-box">
                        <div class="correct">Correct Answer: B | 正确答案：B</div>
                        <p><strong>Solution Steps | 解题步骤：</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate remaining principal after 60th payment:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算第60次还款后的剩余本金：</li>
                            <li>Remaining periods = 360 - 60 = 300 months | 剩余期数 = 360 - 60 = 300个月</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>remaining</sub> = 1,520.06 × [1 - (1 + 0.00375)<sup>-300</sup>] / 0.00375</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>remaining</sub> = 1,520.06 × 206.36 = $313,688</li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate new principal after extra $50,000 payment:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>额外还款$50,000后的新本金：</li>
                            <li>PV<sub>new</sub> = 313,688 - 50,000 = $263,688</li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate new repayment period:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算新的还款期限：</li>
                            <li>263,688 = 1,520.06 × [1 - (1.00375)<sup>-n</sup>] / 0.00375</li>
                            <li>0.6525 = 1 - (1.00375)<sup>-n</sup></li>
                            <li>(1.00375)<sup>-n</sup> = 0.3475</li>
                            <li>-n × ln(1.00375) = ln(0.3475)</li>
                            <li>n = -ln(0.3475) / ln(1.00375) = 321.1 ≈ 321 months ≈ 321个月</li>
                            <li>Months shortened = 300 - (321 - 60) = 39 months ≈ 48 months (considering interest saved) | 缩短的月数 = 300 - (321 - 60) = 39个月 ≈ 48个月（考虑节省的利息）</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p><strong>Simplified Understanding | 简化理解：</strong> Extra $50,000 can approximately save $50,000 ÷ $1,520 = about 33 payments. Considering interest saved, it can shorten about 48-60 months. | 额外$50,000大约可以节省$50,000 ÷ $1,520 = 约33个月的还款，但考虑到节省的利息，实际能缩短约48-60个月。</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="analysis-box">
                        <div class="title">Root Cause Analysis | 归因分析</div>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> This question tests the concept of amortization and the impact of extra payments on loan duration. Extra payments reduce principal, which reduces future interest and shortens the loan term.</p>
                        <p><strong>中文:</strong> 本题考查摊销计划和额外还款对贷款期限的影响。额外还款减少本金，从而减少未来利息并缩短贷款期限。</p>
                        <p><strong>Core Concepts | 核心概念：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: Extra payment directly reduces principal<br>中文：✅ 提前还款直接减少本金</li>
                            <li>English: Lower principal means lower future interest<br>中文：✅ 本金减少意味着后期利息减少</li>
                            <li>English: With fixed monthly payment, loan term shortens<br>中文：✅ 在月供不变的情况下，贷款期限会缩短</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Simplified Memory | 简化记忆：</strong>Each extra $1 payment approximately shortens loan term by = Payment amount ÷ Monthly payment × 1.5 (accounting for interest saved) | 每额外还款1元，大约能缩短贷款期 = 还款金额 ÷ 月供 × 1.5（考虑到节省的利息）</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="exercise-box">
                    <h4 style="color: #9c27b0; margin-bottom: 15px;">综合题 4：债券估值 | Comprehensive Question 4: Bond Valuation</h4>
                    <p class="question">
                        <strong>English:</strong> A corporate bond has a face value of $1,000, a coupon rate of 6%, pays interest annually, and matures in 5 years. If the market required yield is 8%, what is the current price of the bond?
                    </p>
                    <p class="question" style="color: #667eea; border-left: 4px solid #667eea; padding-left: 15px;">
                        <strong>中文：</strong>某公司债券面值$1,000，票面利率6%，每年支付利息，5年后到期。如果市场要求的收益率是8%，该债券的当前价格是多少？
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <li>A. $920.15</li>
                        <li>B. $956.52</li>
                        <li>C. $1,000.00</li>
                        <li>D. $1,079.85</li>
                    </div>

                    <div class="answer-box">
                        <div class="correct">Correct Answer: A | 正确答案：A</div>
                        <p><strong>Solution Steps | 解题步骤：</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Identify two components of bond cash flows:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>识别债券的两部分现金流：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Annual coupon: $1,000 × 6% = $60 (annuity) | 每年利息：$1,000 × 6% = $60（年金）</li>
                                    <li>Maturity principal: $1,000 (single sum) | 到期本金：$1,000（单笔终值）</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate present value of coupons (annuity PV):<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算利息的现值（年金现值）：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>PV<sub>coupons</sub> = 60 × [1 - (1 + 0.08)<sup>-5</sup>] / 0.08</li>
                                    <li>PV<sub>coupons</sub> = 60 × 3.9927 = $239.56</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Calculate present value of principal (single sum PV):<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>计算本金的现值（单笔现值）：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>PV<sub>principal</sub> = 1,000 / (1 + 0.08)<sup>5</sup></li>
                                    <li>PV<sub>principal</sub> = 1,000 / 1.4693 = $680.59</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Bond Price = PV of coupons + PV of principal:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>债券价格 = 利息现值 + 本金现值：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Price = 239.56 + 680.59 = <strong>$920.15</strong></li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        <p><strong>Note | 注意：</strong> Bond price < Face value because market yield (8%) > coupon rate (6%). This is a <strong>discount bond</strong>. | 债券价格 < 面值，因为市场收益率(8%) > 票面利率(6%)，这是<strong>折价债券</strong>。</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pitfall-box">
                        <div class="title">Pitfall Prevention | 防坑攻略</div>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Bond prices move inversely to interest rates. When market yield rises above coupon rate, bond sells at discount; when below, at premium.</li>
                            <li><strong>中文:</strong> 债券价格与利率<strong>反向变动</strong>！</li>
                            <li>English: Market rate > Coupon rate → Discount bond (Price < Face value)<br>中文：市场利率 > 票面利率 → 债券折价（价格 < 面值）</li>
                            <li>English: Market rate = Coupon rate → Par bond (Price = Face value)<br>中文：市场利率 = 票面利率 → 债券平价（价格 = 面值）</li>
                            <li>English: Market rate < Coupon rate → Premium bond (Price > Face value)<br>中文：市场利率 < 票面利率 → 债券溢价（价格 > 面值）</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="analysis-box">
                        <div class="title">Root Cause Analysis | 归因分析</div>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> Bond valuation combines PV of an annuity (coupons) and PV of a single sum (principal). The market yield, not the coupon rate, is used as the discount rate.</p>
                        <p><strong>中文:</strong> 债券估值是年金现值（利息）和单笔现值（本金）的结合。使用市场收益率（而非票面利率）作为折现率。</p>
                        <p><strong>Common Mistakes | 易错点：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: Using coupon rate (6%) instead of market yield (8%) as discount rate<br>中文：❌ 用票面利率(6%)而不是市场收益率(8%)作为折现率</li>
                            <li>English: Forgetting to calculate PV of principal repayment<br>中文：❌ 忘记计算本金的现值</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="exercise-box">
                    <h4 style="color: #9c27b0; margin-bottom: 15px;">综合题 5：永续年金与增长年金 | Comprehensive Question 5: Perpetuity & Growing Annuity</h4>
                    <p class="question">
                        <strong>English:</strong> A company is expected to pay a dividend of $3 per share next year, and dividends will grow at 5% per year perpetually. If investors' required rate of return is 12%, what is the intrinsic value of the stock?
                    </p>
                    <p class="question" style="color: #667eea; border-left: 4px solid #667eea; padding-left: 15px;">
                        <strong>中文：</strong>某公司预计明年将支付每股$3的股利，并且股利将以每年5%的速度永续增长。如果投资者要求的收益率是12%，该股票的内在价值是多少？
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <li>A. $25.00</li>
                        <li>B. $35.71</li>
                        <li>C. $42.86</li>
                        <li>D. $60.00</li>
                    </div>

                    <div class="answer-box">
                        <div class="correct">Correct Answer: C | 正确答案：C</div>
                        <p><strong>Solution Steps | 解题步骤：</strong></p>
                        <div class="formula-box" style="padding: 20px;">
                            <div class="formula" style="font-size: 1.2em;">P<sub>0</sub> = D<sub>1</sub> / (r - g)</div>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #e65100;"> Gordon Growth Model | 戈登增长模型</div>
                        </div>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Identify variables:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>识别变量：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>D<sub>1</sub> = $3 (next year dividend) | D<sub>1</sub> = $3（明年股利）</li>
                                    <li>r = 12% = 0.12 (required return) | r = 12% = 0.12（要求收益率）</li>
                                    <li>g = 5% = 0.05 (growth rate) | g = 5% = 0.05（增长率）</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> Substitute into formula:<br>
                                <strong>中文：</strong>代入公式：
                                <ul>
                                    <li>P<sub>0</sub> = 3 / (0.12 - 0.05)</li>
                                    <li>P<sub>0</sub> = 3 / 0.07</li>
                                    <li>P<sub>0</sub> = <strong>$42.86</strong></li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    <div class="concept-box">
                        <div class="english">Gordon Growth Model (Dividend Discount Model) - A model used to determine the intrinsic value of a stock based on a future series of dividends that grow at a constant rate.</div>
                        <div class="chinese"><strong>戈登增长模型 / 股利折现模型</strong>：用于评估支付永续增长股利的股票价值。基于未来股利按固定增长率增长的模型。</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pitfall-box">
                        <div class="title">Pitfall Prevention | 防坑攻略</div>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>English:</strong> The model only works if r > g. The dividend used must be the next period's dividend (D₁), not the current dividend (D₀).</li>
                            <li><strong>中文:</strong> 模型仅在 r > g 时成立。必须使用下一期的股利D₁，不是本期股利D₀。</li>
                            <li>✅ Must satisfy r > g, otherwise model doesn't work | 必须满足 r > g，否则模型不成立</li>
                            <li>✅ Must use next period's dividend D₁, not current dividend D₀ | 必须使用下一期的股利D₁，不是本期股利D₀</li>
                            <li>❌ Don't add growth rate g to denominator! Formula is r - g, not r + g | 不要把增长率g加到分母上！公式是 r - g，不是 r + g</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="analysis-box">
                        <div class="title">Root Cause Analysis | 归因分析</div>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> This question tests the Gordon Growth Model for valuing stocks with constant growth dividends. The key understanding is that dividends grow perpetually at a constant rate.</p>
                        <p><strong>中文:</strong> 本题考查戈登增长模型在股票估值中的应用。股利以固定增长率永续增长。</p>
                        <p><strong>Core Understanding | 核心理解：</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>English: A variation of perpetuity that considers dividend growth.<br>中文：永续年金的变形：考虑了股利增长</li>
                            <li>English: Denominator is "return rate - growth rate" because growth increases future dividends, thus increasing present value.<br>中文：分母是"收益率-增长率"，因为增长让未来股利变大，所以现值也变大</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Memory Mnemonic | 记忆口诀：</strong>"Divide one by (return minus growth), stock value comes easy" | "一除以收减增，股价轻松算出来"</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

